1. MAC Address Flapping
Scenario

Users report intermittent connectivity.

Logs show:

MAC address xxxx flapping between Gi0/1 and Gi0/2
What would you investigate?
Layer 2 loop
Incorrect cabling
Unmanaged switch connected by user
STP issues
EtherChannel misconfiguration
🔥 2. Broadcast Storm
Scenario

Suddenly:

Switch CPU spikes
Network becomes very slow
Excessive broadcast traffic
What would you check?
STP status
Recent changes
Loops
Storm-control configuration
Interface utilization
🔥 3. STP Root Bridge Changed
Scenario

After maintenance, traffic paths changed and latency increased.

What would you check?
Current root bridge
STP priorities
Newly added switches
Root guard events

Commands:

show spanning-tree
🔥 4. EtherChannel Not Forming
Scenario

Four links configured but Port-Channel remains down.

What would you verify?
Speed
Duplex
Trunk/access mode
Native VLAN
Allowed VLANs
LACP/PAgP mode
STP inconsistencies
🔥 5. Users on Same VLAN Cannot Communicate Across Switches
Scenario

PCs are in the same VLAN but cannot reach each other.

What would you check?
VLAN existence
Trunk status
Allowed VLAN list
STP blocking
MAC learning

Commands:

show vlan brief
show interfaces trunk
show mac address-table
🔥 6. Access Port Goes Err-Disabled
Scenario

A user plugs in a device and the port immediately shuts down.

What would you investigate?
BPDU Guard
Port Security violation
Storm Control action shutdown
UDLD violation

Commands:

show interface status err-disabled
🔥 7. One-Way Traffic Between Switches
Scenario

Traffic works in one direction but not the other.

Common on fiber links.

What would you check?
UDLD status
Fiber Tx/Rx issues
Interface errors
Optics health

Commands:

show udld
show interfaces counters errors
🎯 Interviewer's Expected Troubleshooting Flow

For almost any Layer 2 issue:

Step 1

Check physical layer

show interfaces status
Step 2

Check VLAN / Trunk

show vlan brief
show interfaces trunk
Step 3

Check STP

show spanning-tree
Step 4

Check MAC learning

show mac address-table
Step 5

Check EtherChannel

show etherchannel summary
Step 6

Check Security Features

BPDU Guard
Port Security
DHCP Snooping
Storm Control
UDLD
